'''Adam Ginsberg''' is an [[internet marketer]].  He has promoted software for marketing on [[Myspace]] and training on selling on [[eBay]].
He has written the book ''How to Buy, Sell and Profit on eBay.'',<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.amazon.co.uk/How-Buy-Sell-Profit-eBay/dp/006076287X|title=How to Buy, Sell & Profit on eBay|work=Amazon website|accessdate=22 November 2009| archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20091130090611/http://www.amazon.co.uk/How-Buy-Sell-Profit-eBay/dp/006076287X| archivedate= 30 November 2009 <!--DASHBot-->| deadurl= no}}</ref> along with other titles, which were published by [[Nightingale Conant]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.amazon.co.uk/exec/obidos/search-handle-url?_encoding=UTF8&search-type=ss&index=books-uk&field-author=Adam%20Ginsberg|title=Author Adam Ginsberg|work=Amazon website|accessdate=22 November 2009}}</ref>

Prior to venturing into sales on eBay, Ginsberg ran a business in [[San Diego]] selling [[pool table]]s. Although he claims to have been initially skeptical about selling through eBay, in 2001, he placed a pool table for sale on the service and met success.<ref name="Mello2005-05-01">{{cite journal | last = Mello | first = John P. | date = May 1, 2005  | title = A Skeptic's Transformation to an eBay Fanatic | work = [[The Boston Globe]] | page = E2 |url=http://www.highbeam.com/doc/1P2-7907982.html |via=[[HighBeam]] |subscription=yes}}</ref>

As a result, he continued to engage in eBay sales, expanding his online business and eventually closing his physical store.<ref name="Siskos2003p75">{{cite journal | last = Siskos | first = Catherine | date = July 2003 | title = The Secrets of Power Sellers | work = [[Kiplinger's Personal Finance]] | publisher = Kiplinger Washington Editors, Inc. | volume = 57 | number = 7 | issn = 1528-9729 | page = 75 }}</ref><ref>{{Citation  | last = Tovia  | first = Joanna| title = Smart Ebay traders cash in| newspaper = Daily Telegraph| pages = Pg. 32  | date = August 2, 2005| url = http://www.lexisnexis.com/us/lnacademic/results/docview/docview.do?docLinkInd=true&risb=21_T8063942636&format=GNBFI&sort=RELEVANCE&startDocNo=1&resultsUrlKey=29_T8063942640&cisb=22_T8063942639&treeMax=true&treeWidth=0&csi=244786&docNo=2}}</ref><ref>{{Citation  | last = Lion  | first = Patrick  | title = Selling to the masses on eBay  | newspaper = Daily Telegraph  | pages = Pg. 25  | date = July 26, 2005  | url = http://www.lexisnexis.com/us/lnacademic/results/docview/docview.do?docLinkInd=true&risb=21_T8063942636&format=GNBFI&sort=RELEVANCE&startDocNo=1&resultsUrlKey=29_T8063942640&cisb=22_T8063942639&treeMax=true&treeWidth=0&csi=244786&docNo=7}}
</ref><ref>{{Citation  | last = Roseman  | first = Ellen| title = One man's trash is another's treasure  | newspaper = The Toronto Star  | pages = BUSINESS; Pg. C01  | date = February 29, 2004  | url = http://www.lexisnexis.com/us/lnacademic/results/docview/docview.do?docLinkInd=true&risb=21_T8063942636&format=GNBFI&sort=RELEVANCE&startDocNo=1&resultsUrlKey=29_T8063942640&cisb=22_T8063942639&treeMax=true&treeWidth=0&csi=8286&docNo=25}}</ref>

In 2005 Ginsberg released ''How to buy, sell and profit on eBay''.<ref name="Mello2005-05-01" />

